# MEMORY.md - your auto-loaded index

This is your memory index. The first 200 lines auto-inject every Claude Code session, so keep it tight: one-line pointers grouped by domain, never the topic content itself.

**To activate:** rename this file from `MEMORY.md.template` to `MEMORY.md` and fill in your own pointers.

## Why the section headers matter

A flat list of 40+ memory pointers forces Claude to scan everything to find relevance. Grouping by domain (see the headers below) lets Claude jump straight to the relevant section. This is the highest-ROI organizational fix per the research brief.

